        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6782&amp;FORUM_ID=6&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&amp;Topic_Title=Focus+item+concept%3A+success+or+flop%3F"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I remember all of the hype a few months ago about focus items and how it was supposed to be part of caster balancing. I think it's time to take stock of the impact that these items have had to the game.</P><P>Survey:</P><P>As a necromancer, has the introduction of dropped focus items made any appreciable difference to you?</P><P>As a necromancer, do you actually wear a dropped focus item?</P><P>Are you satisfied that Verant has not retroactively added focus abilities to high level caster gear?</P><P>-----------------------------------------------------------------</P><P>My own opinion on this is that with the exception of the occasional focus item that a mage will summon for me, the concept has failed to address caster balaning in a significant way. I think that thanks to people like Furor (who has no use for necros) focus items are pretty much dead in the water. Focus items as a means to help casters is pretty much a failure. While I do use the mage items *if* I can get my hands on them, the idea that they should be applied to existing items by Verant has not been followed through as they promised they would.</P><P>I think focus items were a great idea to address the fact that casters lost ground to melee classes for 3 expansions. Caster loot has sucked for so long and most of it has had zero impact on our DPS, unlike the many haste items avail for tanks. The Centi Longsword single-handedly has increased the damage by wars, rangers, pallies, SKs and rogues by a big margin and has trickled down to most twinks. There are no comparable items such as haste and weapons that have had this kind of impact on casters.</P><P>Verant please keep your promise and continue to modify existing high level caster gear with lvl 3 focus effects.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless</font></td>

