        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Focus items seem to have been forgotten since they were introduced.</P><P>Personally I like the idea of focus items a lot. I am very disappointed that as necros we pretty much got shafted, yet again, through a pathetic and bugged line up of dot based focus items.</P><P>Our focus effects are wrong. I posted on this topic a long time ago. We need more. Namely:-</P><P>Dot Compression. Reduce the time a dot takes to do it's damage while not reducing the damage.</P><P>Dot Power. Increase the damage a dot does per tick by 10%.</P><P>I had thought of more but they slip my mind right now. The effects above would all stack with the other focus items.</P><P>Regarding my use of dropped focus items. I wear a serpentine braclet that increases the duration of dots up to level 44 when I am solo fear kiting. I wear it purely because I use dooming darkness as my snare and the difference it makes to the snare duration is easily noticable. If I could get a level 3 item I would wear that but I never have PP to buy or the time to hunt the rare drops.</P><P>I like the "hard choices" that focus items force on us. The serpentine bracer is a perfect example. It's stats are horrible for a necro but it's effect is sweet.</P><P>If I had some other focus items I would wear them - depending on the circumstances. I already have a deluxe sewing kit full of switch gear that I always carry with me.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
